00:17:42,980 --> 00:18:02,980
 [ Music ]

212
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:14,980
 In the bleak midwinter, frosty wind made moan.

213
00:18:14,980 --> 00:18:26,980
 Earth stood hard as iron, water like a stone.

214
00:18:27,980 --> 00:18:38,980
 Snow had fallen, snow on snow, snow on snow.

215
00:18:38,980 --> 00:18:51,980
 In the bleak midwinter long ago.

216
00:18:54,980 --> 00:19:05,980
 Heaven cannot hold him, nor earth sustain.

217
00:19:05,980 --> 00:19:17,980
 Heaven and earth shall flee away when he comes to reign.

218
00:19:18,980 --> 00:19:29,980
 In the bleak midwinter, stable place survives.

219
00:19:29,980 --> 00:19:41,980
 Lord God Almighty, Jesus Christ.

220
00:19:45,980 --> 00:19:56,980
 What can I give him, poor as I am?

221
00:19:56,980 --> 00:20:08,980
 If I were a shepherd, I would bring the lamb.

222
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:20,980
 If I were a wise man, I would do my part.

223
00:20:20,980 --> 00:20:32,980
 What I can I give him, give my heart.

224
00:20:33,980 --> 00:20:45,980
 What can I give him, give my heart.

225
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:52,980
 I love that final line or the final stanza of the hymn.

226
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:54,980
 Let me read it to you one more time.

227
00:20:54,980 --> 00:20:56,980
 What can I give him, as poor as I am?

228
00:20:56,980 --> 00:20:58,980
 If I were a shepherd, I would bring a lamb.

229
00:20:58,980 --> 00:21:00,980
 If I were a wise man, I would do my part.

230
00:21:01,980 --> 00:21:04,980
 What I can give him, is I can give him my heart.

231
00:21:04,980 --> 00:21:12,980
 Beautiful message of Christmas there, but I think also leaning into what Luke is trying to say to us in the passage we're looking at this morning.

232
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:14,980
 We are to give Jesus our heart.

233
00:21:14,980 --> 00:21:18,980
 The challenge is, what heart are you giving him?

234
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:22,980
 Is it a heart that's big enough to receive all that he is?

235
00:21:22,980 --> 00:21:29,980
 Or a heart so small that you're expecting him to reduce himself to you?

236
00:21:30,980 --> 00:21:37,980
 It is this that basically Simeon is filled with as he speaks out over Israel.

237
00:21:37,980 --> 00:21:44,980
 Let me read to you one more time these words that Simeon prophesies over Jesus and the people in the temple.

238
00:21:44,980 --> 00:21:49,980
 He says, "Sovereign Lord, as you have promised, you can now dismiss your servant in peace.

239
00:21:49,980 --> 00:21:56,980
 For my eyes have indeed seen your salvation, which you have prepared in the sight of all the people.

240
00:21:57,980 --> 00:22:03,980
 A light for revelation to the Gentiles and a glory to your people Israel."

241
00:22:03,980 --> 00:22:11,980
 It's beautiful to me that Simeon filled with the Spirit comes and says something that actually the Jewish people were not expecting.

242
00:22:11,980 --> 00:22:16,980
 If we step back from the moment and just look at the history that leads us to it.

243
00:22:16,980 --> 00:22:21,980
 As I said earlier, that there's been a 400 year waiting period for this moment.

244
00:22:22,980 --> 00:22:29,980
 400 years where the last prophecy in Malachi in the Old Testament to this moment where Simeon prophesies in the temple.

245
00:22:29,980 --> 00:22:31,980
 That's a long period of time.

246
00:22:31,980 --> 00:22:38,980
 And during that time the Jewish people had constructed for themselves this Messiah that they were longing to come.

247
00:22:38,980 --> 00:22:44,980
 And they had thought about what is it that they want this Messiah to be when he does arrive.

248
00:22:44,980 --> 00:22:51,980
 And the three primary focuses for the Jewish people in the first century as they prayed and longed for the Messiah were this.

249
00:22:51,980 --> 00:22:56,980
 Number one, that when the Messiah comes the Romans will be pushed away.

250
00:22:56,980 --> 00:23:03,980
 The oppression that we're under, under the Romans would finish and the Romans would rule us no more.

251
00:23:03,980 --> 00:23:07,980
 Number two, when the Messiah comes sin will be suddenly dealt with.

252
00:23:07,980 --> 00:23:13,980
 It'll be like an apocalyptic moment where the world will be changed in an instant and sin will be no more.

253
00:23:13,980 --> 00:23:19,980
 And when the Messiah comes we the Jewish people would have our rightful place again.

254
00:23:20,980 --> 00:23:24,980
 We're ruling here in the world with our right land and our right context.

255
00:23:24,980 --> 00:23:28,980
 So this idea of Romans be gone, sin be gone.

256
00:23:28,980 --> 00:23:33,980
 And for us to have a place of power and leadership for ourselves once again.

257
00:23:33,980 --> 00:23:37,980
 This was what was wrapped up in the desire for the Messiah.

258
00:23:37,980 --> 00:23:44,980
 Now think also this is the first moment that the Messiah is proclaimed publicly in Israel.

259
00:23:44,980 --> 00:23:49,980
 Remember the angels had come and proclaimed the Messiah over the shepherds.

260
00:23:49,980 --> 00:23:53,980
 And the shepherds had gone to see Jesus in the stable.

261
00:23:53,980 --> 00:23:59,980
 The star had shone in the sky which enabled the Magi to journey towards Jesus bringing their gifts.

262
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:03,980
 And able to do that before him in the stable.

263
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:10,980
 But 40 days later this is the first time that God decides to make a public announcement about the Messiah.

264
00:24:10,980 --> 00:24:18,980
 And who the Messiah is and he's doing that announcement in the very center of what the Jewish culture and religious culture.

265
00:24:18,980 --> 00:24:22,980
 And religious sort of hub was of the day right there in the temple.

266
00:24:22,980 --> 00:24:28,980
 And notice what God by his spirit inspires Simeon to say first.

267
00:24:28,980 --> 00:24:31,980
 The first thing that comes out of his mouth is this.

268
00:24:31,980 --> 00:24:36,980
 This Messiah is a light of revelation to the Gentiles.

269
00:24:36,980 --> 00:24:44,980
 You can almost imagine you could have heard a pin drop in that room.

270
00:24:44,980 --> 00:24:46,980
 This is the temple.

271
00:24:47,980 --> 00:24:50,980
 This is the seat of Jewish power.

272
00:24:50,980 --> 00:24:53,980
 This is where they've been longing and praying and hoping for.

273
00:24:53,980 --> 00:24:57,980
 And there's Simeon and the first thing he says is you want to know who the Messiah is.

274
00:24:57,980 --> 00:24:59,980
 You want to know what this Jesus is.

275
00:24:59,980 --> 00:25:02,980
 He's going to be a light of revelation to the Gentiles.

276
00:25:02,980 --> 00:25:04,980
 Isn't that great?

277
00:25:04,980 --> 00:25:11,980
 And you can imagine the people standing around him saying whoa hang on hang on a sec.

278
00:25:12,980 --> 00:25:18,980
 The Gentiles, the ones who rule over us, the ones who are oppressing us.

279
00:25:18,980 --> 00:25:22,980
 This one is going to be a light of revelation to them.

280
00:25:22,980 --> 00:25:26,980
 That doesn't sound like grace.

281
00:25:26,980 --> 00:25:30,980
 It's funny isn't it? Grace is only ever amazing when it's grace for us.

282
00:25:33,980 --> 00:25:41,980
 When we find out that grace is for our enemy, for our oppressor, for the one who has enslaved us.

283
00:25:41,980 --> 00:25:44,980
 You're telling me that the Messiah, this is the first thing.

284
00:25:44,980 --> 00:25:46,980
 Notice God here.

285
00:25:46,980 --> 00:25:51,980
 This is the first thing that's announced to the Jewish power and authority and the priests and the people.

286
00:25:51,980 --> 00:25:55,980
 That Jesus is going to be the Messiah that you did not expect.

287
00:25:55,980 --> 00:25:58,980
 You thought the Messiah was going to push away the Gentiles.

288
00:25:58,980 --> 00:26:01,980
 You thought this was all about your re-enthronement.

289
00:26:02,980 --> 00:26:05,980
 No no no, the Messiah, yes there's going to be glory to Israel which is what he says second.

290
00:26:05,980 --> 00:26:09,980
 But the first thing he says is here's what you need to know about Jesus.

291
00:26:09,980 --> 00:26:13,980
 Because if you don't know this about Jesus, Jewish people, you're going to miss him completely.

292
00:26:13,980 --> 00:26:21,980
 He's coming to show grace and mercy and love and revelation and bring change to the ones that you currently hate.

293
00:26:21,980 --> 00:26:30,980
 I mean talk about God breaking open some boxes that his people had put Jesus in.

294
00:26:31,980 --> 00:26:34,980
 Oh it needs to look like this.

295
00:26:34,980 --> 00:26:42,980
 God says the first thing you need to know, it's going to look nothing like you thought it was going to look.

296
00:26:42,980 --> 00:26:49,980
 And if you don't realize it now, you're going to completely miss out.

297
00:26:49,980 --> 00:26:55,980
 It's interesting because Jesus then in his ministry, as he begins to inaugurate the kingdom of God,

298
00:26:55,980 --> 00:27:00,980
 as he begins to show that through the miracles he does, as he begins to do that through the teaching that he does,

299
00:27:00,980 --> 00:27:04,980
 often in parables, he would end those teachings saying if you have ears to hear, let him hear.

300
00:27:04,980 --> 00:27:07,980
 If you can see with eyes, let you see.

301
00:27:07,980 --> 00:27:11,980
 In other words, I am here, I'm the Messiah, I'm the fullness of what you've ever had.

302
00:27:11,980 --> 00:27:15,980
 But it looks different to the thing that you have created me for.

303
00:27:15,980 --> 00:27:21,980
 And unless you are enabled to expand what you thought and embrace the new, you're going to completely miss out.

304
00:27:21,980 --> 00:27:25,980
 This is why Jesus, when he's standing over Jerusalem at the end of his ministry,

305
00:27:26,980 --> 00:27:30,980
 and the triumphal entry, looking over the temple as well up on the hill,

306
00:27:30,980 --> 00:27:35,980
 he says in the final five days of his life, he's looking at that temple and he says this.

307
00:27:35,980 --> 00:27:41,980
 He says, "If only you knew who it was that was coming to you now, the Prince of Peace coming to you."

308
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:44,980
 But he says, "It is hidden from you.

309
00:27:44,980 --> 00:27:51,980
 You put me in a box and you're refusing to accept me if I don't fit into your box."

310
00:27:51,980 --> 00:27:54,980
 But guess what? It's not about me fitting into your box.

311
00:27:55,980 --> 00:27:57,980
 It's about your box getting smashed.

312
00:27:57,980 --> 00:28:06,980
 This is the prophetic word to Israel right at the inauguration of Jesus' dedication in the temple.

313
00:28:06,980 --> 00:28:16,980
 "Your box that you have placed me in, if you do not smash that box, you will miss out."

314
00:28:17,980 --> 00:28:26,980
 In other words, it was almost like God was saying, "You are not prepared, Israel, for the receiving of the Messiah."

315
00:28:26,980 --> 00:28:30,980
 And I'm bringing a prophetic word through Simeon to you right now.

316
00:28:30,980 --> 00:28:37,980
 That if you can hear it, if you can open your heart to it, you will see Jesus bigger.

317
00:28:37,980 --> 00:28:42,980
 You will see your Messiah far bigger and far grander than you could ever see him.

318
00:28:43,980 --> 00:28:51,980
 He is more glorious, more powerful, more saving, more loving, more graceful, more merciful than you had ever thought he was.

319
00:28:51,980 --> 00:28:59,980
 He is going to be an even greater glory to Israel if you would just let him out of your box.

320
00:28:59,980 --> 00:29:02,980
 It's like he's kind of wanting to take a hammer.

321
00:29:02,980 --> 00:29:05,980
 I'm going to do this for you. I'm going to move this out of the way.

322
00:29:05,980 --> 00:29:09,980
 It's like he wants to take a hammer to this box and do this.

323
00:29:10,980 --> 00:29:13,980
 No, I'm not going to do that. It's my wife's.

324
00:29:13,980 --> 00:29:16,980
 This is my wife's jewelry box, okay?

325
00:29:16,980 --> 00:29:21,980
 She's currently on holiday in New Zealand. She would be very upset if I smashed her jewelry box.

326
00:29:21,980 --> 00:29:26,980
 But that's, it's like you need glasses in the front row.

327
00:29:26,980 --> 00:29:33,980
 But that's essentially what God is doing through Simeon to Israel in this moment.

328
00:29:33,980 --> 00:29:38,980
 And I want to say a couple of things to us today in connection to that.

329
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:42,980
 Number one, I don't think it's just Israel that puts Jesus in a box.

330
00:29:42,980 --> 00:29:45,980
 I think we all have the tendency to do it.

331
00:29:45,980 --> 00:29:51,980
 Number two, in the same way that I think Simeon was this prophetic declaration to Israel,

332
00:29:51,980 --> 00:29:55,980
 you are not yet prepared for the Messiah that is coming.

333
00:29:55,980 --> 00:29:57,980
 And if you don't get ready, you're going to miss.

334
00:29:57,980 --> 00:30:01,980
 I want to say this boldly to some of you in this room, and this will resonate with some of you.

335
00:30:01,980 --> 00:30:06,980
 You are not yet prepared for the Jesus of 2026 in your life.

336
00:30:07,980 --> 00:30:10,980
 And you need to break him out of the box you placed him in.

337
00:30:10,980 --> 00:30:15,980
 Otherwise, you will miss out on all the things that he might have for you in 2026.

338
00:30:15,980 --> 00:30:21,980
 You see, we place Jesus in boxes all the time in our life.

339
00:30:21,980 --> 00:30:27,980
 I think we have the box of limitations, where we limit the power of Jesus down,

340
00:30:27,980 --> 00:30:30,980
 and we say, "I don't think Jesus could touch that part of my life.

341
00:30:30,980 --> 00:30:35,980
 I don't think he could heal me of that. I don't think he could address that situation in my life."

342
00:30:36,980 --> 00:30:39,980
 "It's been a long time. Nothing's ever happened. I just don't think he can do it."

343
00:30:39,980 --> 00:30:41,980
 Boxes of limitations.

344
00:30:41,980 --> 00:30:44,980
 We have boxes of experience.

345
00:30:44,980 --> 00:30:46,980
 "Well, Jesus has never done that for me."

346
00:30:46,980 --> 00:30:50,980
 "Oh, he might have done that for you. That's good. That's nice. That's your testimony, but that's not my experience."

347
00:30:50,980 --> 00:30:58,980
 And we limit the power of Jesus in our lives, and we place him in a box because of our experience of him.

348
00:30:58,980 --> 00:31:01,980
 I think we have boxes of culture.

349
00:31:01,980 --> 00:31:05,980
 "Oh, this is how I do things. This is how my people do things.

350
00:31:05,980 --> 00:31:09,980
 This is the way of our culture, and Jesus doesn't fit to that culture,

351
00:31:09,980 --> 00:31:13,980
 and I think we need to shift Jesus and make him look a little bit more like us,

352
00:31:13,980 --> 00:31:16,980
 rather than make myself look more like him."

353
00:31:16,980 --> 00:31:21,980
 And Jesus comes and gives us the culture of the kingdom of God,

354
00:31:21,980 --> 00:31:24,980
 one that can be seen and flourishing in all cultures in this world,

355
00:31:24,980 --> 00:31:28,980
 but one that needs to be a new culture for each one.

356
00:31:28,980 --> 00:31:31,980
 Or perhaps we have boxes of theology.

357
00:31:31,980 --> 00:31:34,980
 "Oh, yeah. Oh, this is how I know Jesus is.

358
00:31:34,980 --> 00:31:37,980
 I mean, I've read the scriptures. This is it. I know it. It's like this.

359
00:31:37,980 --> 00:31:39,980
 It's a tight little thing like this."

360
00:31:39,980 --> 00:31:44,980
 And sometimes our theological boxes can actually contain him down,

361
00:31:44,980 --> 00:31:49,980
 rather than keep him mysterious and marvelous and amazing.

362
00:31:49,980 --> 00:31:53,980
 Simeon speaks out a bold word to his people.

363
00:31:53,980 --> 00:31:56,980
 He's going to be the light of revelation to the Gentiles.

364
00:31:56,980 --> 00:32:00,980
 "You need to open your box," he's saying. "Smash it. Change it.

365
00:32:01,980 --> 00:32:02,980
 Jesus is different."

366
00:32:02,980 --> 00:32:06,980
 This is why Paul, when he writes to the church in Ephesus, chapter 3, says,

367
00:32:06,980 --> 00:32:12,980
 "Jesus, this one, is able to do immeasurably more than you could ever ask or imagine."

368
00:32:12,980 --> 00:32:15,980
 Don't limit him down. He can do immeasurably more.

369
00:32:15,980 --> 00:32:20,980
 "So that his glory would be seen in Christ Jesus and in the church," he says.

370
00:32:20,980 --> 00:32:24,980
 And there's Jesus himself ministering to the people,

371
00:32:24,980 --> 00:32:28,980
 constantly challenging the boxes that they place the Messiah in,

372
00:32:29,980 --> 00:32:33,980
 constantly challenging the old traditions and laws that have hemmed him in,

373
00:32:33,980 --> 00:32:36,980
 and constantly standing before the people and saying, "I'm with you now.

374
00:32:36,980 --> 00:32:41,980
 Come and see and taste all of you who are weary and burdened.

375
00:32:41,980 --> 00:32:43,980
 Come to me and I will give you rest.

376
00:32:43,980 --> 00:32:49,980
 I am bigger and more grander and more powerful than you have created the box for me to be.

377
00:32:49,980 --> 00:32:51,980
 Smash your box."

378
00:32:51,980 --> 00:32:58,980
 And I can't think of a more important word as we finish 2025 and as we move into 2026

379
00:32:58,980 --> 00:33:03,980
 that God would stand over you today, maybe with the same prophetic utterance,

380
00:33:03,980 --> 00:33:06,980
 and say, "You've placed me too much in a box.

381
00:33:06,980 --> 00:33:09,980
 I am far bigger than how you currently see me.

382
00:33:09,980 --> 00:33:12,980
 Are you willing to open your eyes?

383
00:33:12,980 --> 00:33:18,980
 For those who have eyes, let them see, and those who have ears, let them hear."

384
00:33:18,980 --> 00:33:21,980
 Can I pray for you? Let's pray.

385
00:33:24,980 --> 00:33:30,980
 Father, we are humbled by this beautiful part of the Christmas story,

386
00:33:30,980 --> 00:33:35,980
 where the very first utterance publicly over Israel is to say,

387
00:33:35,980 --> 00:33:40,980
 "This Savior is the Savior for the ones that you do not want to have a Savior."

388
00:33:40,980 --> 00:33:45,980
 This Messiah is big enough to offer love and mercy and forgiveness

389
00:33:45,980 --> 00:33:48,980
 to even those who you consider your enemies.

390
00:33:48,980 --> 00:33:53,980
 The grace is so much bigger than you thought.

391
00:33:54,980 --> 00:34:02,980
 And Father, I want to pray for each of us as we finish off 2025 and prepare ourselves for 2026.

392
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:07,980
 As this week on Wednesday and Thursday, we celebrate the arrival of Jesus.

393
00:34:07,980 --> 00:34:13,980
 Lord, we want to go into that process aware of the boxes that we placed you in,

394
00:34:13,980 --> 00:34:20,980
 where we've limited you because of our experience or our culture or our theology.

395
00:34:21,980 --> 00:34:26,980
 Because we try to sort you out and create a nice, neat little box for you to fit in.

396
00:34:26,980 --> 00:34:32,980
 And Lord, I do believe that there are people in this room who are not yet prepared

397
00:34:32,980 --> 00:34:38,980
 for the incredible things that you want to do in their lives in the year ahead.

398
00:34:38,980 --> 00:34:41,980
 And you're saying, "Would you smash the box?

399
00:34:41,980 --> 00:34:44,980
 Would you open your heart more?

400
00:34:44,980 --> 00:34:47,980
 Would you not be so skeptical?

401
00:34:48,980 --> 00:34:53,980
 Would you believe that I am grander and bigger than you've ever thought?

402
00:34:53,980 --> 00:34:57,980
 That I am immeasurably more than you could ever ask or imagine?

403
00:34:57,980 --> 00:35:00,980
 And I am that for you.

404
00:35:00,980 --> 00:35:04,980
 And this is not about you changing me to fit your comfortable life.

405
00:35:04,980 --> 00:35:10,980
 It's about me challenging you to change you to walk into the best life.

406
00:35:10,980 --> 00:35:17,980
 So Holy Spirit, I want to pray for anyone in this room where this message is resonating with them.

407
00:35:18,980 --> 00:35:21,980
 As we're in this transition time between one year to the next.

408
00:35:21,980 --> 00:35:25,980
 Father, as a church community, we want to move, Lord,

409
00:35:25,980 --> 00:35:33,980
 into the year with no more boxes, no more limitations.

410
00:35:33,980 --> 00:35:36,980
 Nothing limited by experience or culture or theology,

411
00:35:36,980 --> 00:35:43,980
 but an openness in spirit and heart for more of you.

412
00:35:44,980 --> 00:35:49,980
 Would you be a light of revelation to us, the Gentiles in this room?

413
00:35:49,980 --> 00:35:55,980
 Would you reveal yourself in grander and bigger ways than we could ever have imagined?

414
00:35:55,980 --> 00:36:03,980
 And may our worship of you expand beyond what my heart currently says about you.

415
00:36:03,980 --> 00:36:09,980
 Would you show me things about you that would set my heart on fire, Lord?

416
00:36:11,980 --> 00:36:16,980
 I am not satisfied with the Jesus I currently know.

417
00:36:16,980 --> 00:36:21,980
 As grateful as I am for it, would you be more, Lord?

418
00:36:21,980 --> 00:36:27,980
 Would you open me to fresh wind, new wine?

419
00:36:27,980 --> 00:36:31,980
 Would you make in me a new wineskin?

420
00:36:31,980 --> 00:36:34,980
 And would it be for your glory?

421
00:36:34,980 --> 00:36:37,980
 We pray this in Jesus' name.

422
00:36:38,980 --> 00:36:44,980
 Would you stand with me as we respond together as a community in worship?

423
00:36:44,980 --> 00:36:46,980
 [MUSIC]

